1
00:04:13,986 --> 00:04:15,920
查理
Charlie!

2
00:04:22,761 --> 00:04:25,730
我担心你赶不上这班巴士
I wasn't so sure you'd be on the bus.

3
00:04:25,998 --> 00:04:28,558
不想让你的白人弟兄们误以为
Didn't want your white brothers
thinking 

4
00:04:28,700 --> 00:04:31,100
你是我们族里最优秀的人才
you were the best we had.

5
00:05:16,214 --> 00:05:19,183
“所罗门群岛1943年”
SOLOMON ISLANDS
1943

6
00:05:32,331 --> 00:05:34,060
小心!
Watch out!

7
00:05:39,338 --> 00:05:41,238
我的手!
My hand!

8
00:06:01,860 --> 00:06:03,725
他妈的!
Goddamn!

9
00:06:05,097 --> 00:06:08,362
快没子弹了
我们得快走
We're running out of ammo.
We gotta get out of here.

10
00:06:15,841 --> 00:06:17,638
前进!
Move!

11
00:06:32,824 --> 00:06:34,052
过来!
Come on!

12
00:06:36,461 --> 00:06:39,157
过来,你办得到的!
Come on, you can do it! Come on!

13
00:06:56,681 --> 00:06:59,650
完全没弹药了,恩得斯!
我们没弹药了!
We got nothin', Enders!
We're out of ammo!

14
00:07:00,285 --> 00:07:04,187
乔伊,我们不该再平白牺牲
现在撤退还来得及!
Joe... Nobody else needs to die.
We can go! We can get outta here!

15
00:07:10,529 --> 00:07:11,928
我们身负任务!
We got orders!

16
00:07:12,063 --> 00:07:15,590
上面要我们守住这个点!
我们就得死守在这里!
They told us to hold the position!
And that's what we're gonna do!

17
00:07:25,677 --> 00:07:28,669
起来,阿兵哥!
死守下去!
Get up, marine!
Hold the goddamn position!

18
00:07:33,418 --> 00:07:35,318
拼啦!
Come on!

19
00:07:36,388 --> 00:07:38,219
趴下!
Get down!

20
00:07:42,727 --> 00:07:44,661
汤米
Tommy.

21
00:07:46,531 --> 00:07:48,726
该死的砘!
Goddamn you!

22
00:07:54,673 --> 00:07:56,368
不!
Oh, no! No!

23
00:08:09,588 --> 00:08:11,715
-比尔!
-我没子弹了
- Bill!
- I'm out.

24
00:08:16,194 --> 00:08:18,287
过来!
Come on! Come on!

25
00:08:32,277 --> 00:08:34,643
你他妈的,乔伊恩得斯!
Goddamn you, Joe Enders.

26
00:08:36,414 --> 00:08:38,177
不!
No... No!

27
00:08:38,884 --> 00:08:42,911
不!
No!

28
00:08:54,599 --> 00:08:56,624
右手举起来
Raise your right hand.

29
00:08:56,768 --> 00:09:00,329
-我…说自己的名字…
-我,班亚吉…
- I... State your full name...
- I, Ben Yahzee...

30
00:09:01,706 --> 00:09:04,800
彭德尔顿营,加利福尼亚
CAMP PENDLETON, CALIFORNIA

31
00:09:05,010 --> 00:09:09,640
兹誓言支持并保护美国宪法
..do solemnly swear to support and
defend the constitution of the US...

32
00:09:09,814 --> 00:09:14,845
抵御任何敌人
不论国内或国外…
..against all enemies,
foreign and domestic...
..against all enemies,
foreign and domestic...

33
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:18,456
日本人称之为“箱子”
谁知道“坦克”的密码?
Jap Ha-Go. Who can give me
the code word for "tank"?

34
00:09:26,865 --> 00:09:29,299
你们想成为密码战士
Come on. You boys
wanna be codetalkers.

35
00:09:29,968 --> 00:09:32,198
那就要有脑袋啊,快想!
Show me some brains. Think!

36
00:09:32,637 --> 00:09:34,764
我们怎么说坦克?
What do we call a tank?

37
00:09:39,010 --> 00:09:40,534
Chay-da-gahi.

38
00:09:43,715 --> 00:09:46,047
乌龟,很好
Tortoise. Good.

39
00:09:48,420 --> 00:09:50,445
大炮,密码?
Artillery. Code word?

40
00:09:54,359 --> 00:09:56,418
请说密码,白马二等兵
In code. Private Whitehorse.

41
00:09:57,062 --> 00:09:59,189
Be-al-doh-tso-lani?

42
00:10:01,132 --> 00:10:02,724
很好
Very good.

43
00:10:02,867 --> 00:10:04,767
日本零式战机,密码?
Japanese Zero. Code word?

44
00:10:05,236 --> 00:10:09,229
“肯尼欧湾美国海军医院
1943”
KANEOHE BAY US NAVAL HOSPITAL
1943

45
00:10:40,071 --> 00:10:42,904
现在撤退还来得及!
We can go! We can get outta here!

46
00:10:43,041 --> 00:10:45,100
上面要我们守住这个点!
They told us to hold the position!

47
00:10:59,991 --> 00:11:01,925
天气真好啊
Nice day, huh?

48
00:11:02,661 --> 00:11:04,322
乔伊?
Joe?

49
00:11:15,206 --> 00:11:16,730
乔伊?
Joe.

50
00:11:23,314 --> 00:11:24,713
你根本没听到
我在说话,对吧?
Didn't hear a word, did you?

51
00:11:24,883 --> 00:11:28,444
男人碰到美女不都是这样
That's what happens to a man
when he's talking to a beautiful woman.

52
00:11:28,586 --> 00:11:31,749
你不读我的唇语才会这样
It happens when you're
not watching my lips, Joe.

53
00:11:37,128 --> 00:11:39,062
看我
Watch this.

54
00:11:58,550 --> 00:12:02,008
你还没康复,骗不了人的
You're a mess, Joe.
You're not fooling anybody.

55
00:12:02,187 --> 00:12:04,519
不,丽塔,他才是还没康复
No, Rita. He's a mess.

56
00:12:07,058 --> 00:12:08,548
我每天都在康复中
I'm getting better every day.

57
00:12:08,693 --> 00:12:12,857
你中耳破损,平衡感不正常
You got a perforated eardrum, Enders.
Your equilibrium's all screwy.

58
00:12:12,997 --> 00:12:15,989
站都站不起来怎么重回战场
You can't go back to war
if you can't stand up.

59
00:12:16,134 --> 00:12:20,036
走吧,胜利不会从天上掉下来
Let's go, marines. This war
ain't gonna wait forever. Let's go.

60
00:12:22,407 --> 00:12:23,499
乔伊?
Joe...

61
00:12:43,361 --> 00:12:45,659
为什么你不好好留下来?
Why don't you just stay here, Joe?

62
00:12:48,733 --> 00:12:51,224
总得有人留下来陪妇女救护团
Somebody's gotta keep
the WAVES company.

63
00:12:52,771 --> 00:12:54,932
到底帮不帮我?
Are you gonna help me or not?

64
00:13:40,985 --> 00:13:42,179
“丧失听力”

65
00:13:48,193 --> 00:13:49,751
改善很多了
Marked improvement.

66
00:13:50,161 --> 00:13:52,789
他左耳情况比较差吗?
And his left ear is the worse of the two?

67
00:14:13,084 --> 00:14:15,951
好得真快
It's... amazing.

68
00:14:27,031 --> 00:14:29,693
TBY型的范围比不上TBX
TBY hasn't got the range of the TBX.

69
00:14:29,968 --> 00:14:33,369
所以讯号可能要分程传递
So you may need a relay to get
your transmission to command post.

70
00:14:33,504 --> 00:14:37,770
但重点是压力下的速度与精准
But what it really comes down to
is speed and accuracy under pressure.

71
00:14:38,843 --> 00:14:40,902
开始解读
Transcribe now.

72
00:14:41,079 --> 00:14:43,809
维多,里是X光,完毕
Victor, Victor. This is X-ray. Over.

73
00:14:51,789 --> 00:14:54,383
可恶!我方弟兄遭炮火攻击!
Damn it! We got a unit under fire!

74
00:14:54,993 --> 00:14:56,654
伤亡惨重
We're losing men.

75
00:14:56,794 --> 00:14:58,989
请解读这段讯息
I need this message decrypted.

76
00:15:05,103 --> 00:15:10,040
“请求炮火支援,
目标在119,B15”
"Request fire support. We have target
at one-one-niner, Baker one-five."

77
00:15:10,174 --> 00:15:13,143
“碉堡有重机枪
请立刻开火”
"Pillbox with heavy machine gun.
Fire at will."

78
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:20,574
初学者手气好
Beginner's luck.

79
00:15:49,747 --> 00:15:51,647
换你了,大哥
You're up, mac.

80
00:15:56,454 --> 00:15:59,389
-恩得斯下士报到,长官
-稍息
- Corporal Enders reporting, sir.
- At ease.

81
00:16:06,164 --> 00:16:08,724
你的表现相当不错,下士
You've done well as a marine, Corporal.

82
00:16:09,534 --> 00:16:11,968
比从军前的行为好多了
Better than you did as a civilian.

83
00:16:12,103 --> 00:16:16,335
偷窃撞毁机车
遭高中勒令退学
Stole a motorbike, crashed it.
Got kicked out of high school.

84
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:21,876
袭击并殴打克里宾欧唐诺神父
Assault and battery...
on one Father Crispin O'Donnell?

85
00:16:23,548 --> 00:16:25,539
连教士都打?
A priest?

86
00:16:25,683 --> 00:16:30,382
他是齐纳主教高中副校长
兼训导主任
Assistant principal at Archbishop Keenan
High School, sir, and head disciplinarian.

87
00:16:31,589 --> 00:16:33,750
我以前念的是公立学校
Public-school boy myself.

88
00:16:35,093 --> 00:16:37,527
训练中心时还是小错不断
Some minor problems in boot.

89
00:16:38,730 --> 00:16:41,221
在上海获颁最佳勇气奖
A commendation for valor in Shanghai.

90
00:16:41,699 --> 00:16:44,827
死守所罗门群岛表现杰出
And you made a hell of a stand
on the Solomons.

91
00:16:44,969 --> 00:16:46,994
那儿很苦吧?
Tough bit of business there, huh?

92
00:16:47,739 --> 00:16:49,366
相当艰苦,长官
Pretty tough, sir.

93
00:16:50,408 --> 00:16:52,740
可是,你想再回去?
But you're prepared
to jump right back into it?

94
00:16:53,011 --> 00:16:54,672
是的,长官,非常想
Yes, sir. Very much so.

95
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:58,105
非常想
Very much so.

96
00:16:59,283 --> 00:17:00,807
可是…
Well...

97
00:17:02,687 --> 00:17:07,386
我们的密码全遭日军破解
The Japs have pretty much busted
every code we've thrown at 'em, Corporal.

98
00:17:07,525 --> 00:17:10,517
你在所罗门群岛的弟兄
因密码被破解全部阵亡
You men on the Solomons
were lost to a broken code.

99
00:17:10,995 --> 00:17:15,227
在所罗门碰到过印地安人吗?
Tell me something. You ever
run into any Indians on the Solomons?

100
00:17:15,366 --> 00:17:18,358
-印地安人,长官?
-正确的说,应该是纳瓦荷人
- Indians, sir?
- Navajo, to be exact.

101
00:17:19,270 --> 00:17:23,104
军方用他们的语言
发展出一套新密码
The Corps has developed a new code
based on their language.

102
00:17:23,241 --> 00:17:25,141
评价相当不错
It's had quite an impact.

103
00:17:25,276 --> 00:17:29,269
所以海军总部下令全力保护它
So much so the navy have decided
to go to great lengths to protect it.

104
00:17:29,680 --> 00:17:31,580
这就是找你来的原因
That's why you're here.

105
00:17:32,383 --> 00:17:35,750
你将与密码战士配对
全力保护他们
You're to pair with one of them,
keep his ass safe.

106
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:39,083
你负责保护他们的性命
以利他们执行密码任务
Your job is to keep him alive
so he can do his job.

107
00:17:39,624 --> 00:17:43,492
抱歉,我的专长是屠杀日军
Begging the major's pardon, but I believe
I'd best serve the Corps killing Japs,

108
00:17:43,628 --> 00:17:45,528
不是照顾印地安人
not baby-sitting some Indian.

109
00:17:45,663 --> 00:17:48,461
我们不是随便挑到你的
Enders, we didn't pick
your name out of a hat.

110
00:17:49,233 --> 00:17:51,201
我们需要的是杰出陆战队员
We need good marines.

111
00:17:51,702 --> 00:17:53,897
所以才选上你
That's why you're standing here.

112
00:17:54,539 --> 00:17:56,803
你看
Take a look.

113
00:17:56,941 --> 00:17:59,034
他就是个纳瓦荷人…应该死了
It's a Navajo. Or it was.

114
00:17:59,210 --> 00:18:03,078
遭日军逼问密码
严刑拷打致死
Tortured to death by Japanese
intelligence trying to bust our code.

115
00:18:03,214 --> 00:18:06,615
所幸,他想说也说不出所以然
Fortunately, he couldn't help them
even if he wanted to.

116
00:18:07,285 --> 00:18:10,311
-长官?
-他是纳瓦荷人但不是密码战士
- Sir?
- Man's a Navajo, not a codetalker.

117
00:18:10,455 --> 00:18:14,016
密码由他们的语言编成
但毕竟还是密码
Code's based on their language,
but it is still a code.

118
00:18:15,760 --> 00:18:19,093
东条巴不得活捉一个密码战士
Tojo would like nothing more
than to catch a live one.

119
00:18:20,565 --> 00:18:24,296
我以下的话,绝不能漏出去
What I'm about to tell you, Corporal,
cannot leave this room.

120
00:18:25,837 --> 00:18:31,537
不管在任何情况下
密码战士绝不能落入敌人手中
Under no circumstances can you allow
your codetalker to fall into enemy hands.

121
00:18:32,610 --> 00:18:35,511
你的任务是保护密码
Your mission is to protect the code...

122
00:18:37,315 --> 00:18:39,215
不惜任何代价
at all costs.

123
00:18:40,518 --> 00:18:42,452
懂我的意思吗?
You understand me?

124
00:18:45,089 --> 00:18:46,886
是的,长官,我懂
Yes, sir, I do.

125
00:18:47,458 --> 00:18:48,652
很好
Good.

126
00:18:48,793 --> 00:18:51,353
恭喜你,你刚获升中士
Congratulations. You just made sergeant.

127
00:19:43,181 --> 00:19:44,910
手臂保持垂直
Keep those hands vertical.

128
00:19:45,016 --> 00:19:46,916
不错,阿兵哥
Way to go, marine.

129
00:19:53,024 --> 00:19:54,855
佛第诺,接替我一下
Fortino, take over.

130
00:19:57,461 --> 00:20:00,953
少校办公室外的是你,对吧?
Hey... That was you, right,
sitting in front of the major's office?

131
00:20:01,098 --> 00:20:03,293
我叫彼得韩德森
Yeah. Listen, I'm Pete Henderson.

132
00:20:04,268 --> 00:20:08,034
他们叫我公牛
不是因为我的肌肉
They call me Ox.
Not cos of my big muscles or anything.

133
00:20:08,172 --> 00:20:12,268
是因为我住在加州公牛城
好莱坞北边一点点
I'm from Oxnard, California.
Just north of Hollywood a ways.

134
00:20:13,244 --> 00:20:15,405
你也是两栖作战通讯连的人?
So you're with JASCO too, huh?

135
00:20:19,116 --> 00:20:21,676
请问两栖通讯二分队怎么走?
Hey, know where we might find
2nd Joint Assault Signal?

136
00:20:21,786 --> 00:20:22,081
请问两栖通讯二分队怎么走?
Hey, know where we might find
2nd Joint Assault Signal?

137
00:20:22,220 --> 00:20:24,381
没听说过,老土
No fuckin' idea, mac.

138
00:20:25,623 --> 00:20:27,523
多谢
Thanks. Thanks a bunch.

139
00:20:30,895 --> 00:20:34,592
从没看过那么多白人
I've never seen so many white men.

140
00:20:37,268 --> 00:20:40,066
他们也没看过那么多纳瓦荷人
They've never seen so many Navajo.

141
00:20:43,608 --> 00:20:46,600
看起来你上过战场
Looks to me like you got to see
a little action there.

142
00:20:47,578 --> 00:20:49,341
我也是
Me too.

143
00:20:50,414 --> 00:20:52,746
屁股挨了日本鬼子的子弹
Jap sons of bitches
shot me right in the ass.

144
00:20:52,850 --> 00:20:55,978
相不相信?
并不是我想逃避上前线
You believe that shit?
I wasn't running or nothin'.

145
00:20:59,724 --> 00:21:04,991
你在两栖通讯的任务
跟这些纳瓦荷通信兵有关吗?
So, your duty with JASCO have anything
to do with these Navajo radiomen?

146
00:21:07,498 --> 00:21:09,557
我奉命守密
I'm not at liberty to say.

147
00:21:11,502 --> 00:21:14,266
我发现你升官了,我也是
I see you got a new stripe there. Me too.

148
00:21:15,706 --> 00:21:20,803
我猜,你不能说的秘密
跟我不能说的是一样
So I'm guessing the orders you can't tell
me are the same orders I can't tell you.

149
00:21:20,945 --> 00:21:22,572
了不起的任务吧?
Hell of a thing, huh?

150
00:21:22,713 --> 00:21:25,307
身不由己,中士,这里是军队
Ain't a democracy, Sergeant.
It's the marines.

151
00:21:31,088 --> 00:21:33,147
他们看起来蛮正常的
They look pretty normal, I guess.

152
00:21:33,324 --> 00:21:35,622
难道他们得喷上迷彩?
Expecting them to wear war paint?

153
00:21:38,529 --> 00:21:42,863
或许该过去打个招呼
他们好像迷路了
Maybe we ought to go introduce
ourselves. They look a little lost to me.

154
00:21:44,568 --> 00:21:46,627
韩德森
Henderson.

155
00:21:47,438 --> 00:21:49,406
我不想跟他们太亲近
I wouldn't get too friendly.

156
00:21:56,247 --> 00:21:57,214
怎么样?
How!

157
00:21:57,615 --> 00:21:59,446
开个玩笑,我叫公牛
Just kiddin'. I'm Ox.

158
00:21:59,550 --> 00:22:01,245
我叫白马
Whitehorse.

159
00:22:01,385 --> 00:22:03,250
他姓亚吉,叫班
This is Yahzee. Ben.

160
00:22:06,490 --> 00:22:08,390
-下一位
-漂亮
- Next.
- Beautiful. Beautiful.

161
00:22:08,559 --> 00:22:11,756
闭着眼睛会比较好吃
下一个是谁?
Close your eyes. It'll taste better.
Who's next?

162
00:22:50,835 --> 00:22:52,860
可以一起吃吗?
Mind if I join you?

163
00:22:53,671 --> 00:22:57,402
我叫班亚吉,跟你同一组
I'm Ben Yahzee.
Guess the Corps paired us up.

164
00:22:58,275 --> 00:23:00,038
你好吗?
How you doin'?

165
00:23:00,811 --> 00:23:02,904
你挡住我的视线了
You're blocking my view.

166
00:23:06,150 --> 00:23:08,084
对不起
Oh, sorry.

167
00:23:10,054 --> 00:23:12,852
这难吃的东西是什么?
What do they call this crap anyway?

168
00:23:13,023 --> 00:23:14,991
军方称之为食物
Marines call it chow.

169
00:23:16,927 --> 00:23:20,556
有广告不实的嫌疑哦
Well, there's a propaganda effort.

170
00:23:30,574 --> 00:23:32,974
对不起,我的赔你
Sorry. You can have mine.

171
00:23:33,844 --> 00:23:35,607
啊,糟糕
Shit.

172
00:23:42,486 --> 00:23:44,920
